Bromine Trifluoride Last updated Save as PDF Page ID No headers Bromine trifluoride is an interhalogen compound with the formula It is a strawcolored liquid with a pungent odor It is soluble in sulfuric acid but explodes on contact with water and organic compounds It is a powerful fluorinating agent and an ionizing inorganic solvent It is used to produce uranium hexafluoride in the processing and reprocessing of nuclear fuel Topic hierarchy